value.value: Cell-cell signaling in which the ligand is carried between cells by an exosome.
Transynaptic signaling in which the ligand is carried across the synapse by an exosome.

label.value: regulation of recycling endosome localization within postsynapse

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transport or maintenance of location of a postsynaptic recycling endosome within the postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of modification of postsynaptic structure

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of modification of postsynaptic structure.
The intermediate filament cytoskeleton that is part of a postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of presynaptic dense core granule exocytosis

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of presynaptic dense core granule exocytosis.

label.value: regulation of neurotransmitter loading into synaptic vesicle

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter loading into synaptic vesicles.
Cell-cell signaling to or from a synapse, mediated by nitric oxide.

label.value: postsynaptic specialization membrane of symmetric synapse

value.value: The membrane component of the postsynaptic specialization of a symmetric synapse. This is the region of the postsynaptic membrane in which the population of neurotransmitter receptors involved in synaptic transmission are concentrated.

label.value: postsynaptic specialization of symmetric synapse, intracellular component

value.value: A network of proteins adjacent to the postsynaptic membrane of a symmetric synapse. Its major components include that spatially and functionally organize neurotransmitter receptors in the adjacent membrane, such as anchoring and scaffolding molecules, signaling enzymes and cytoskeletal components. This structure is not as thick or electron dense as the postsynaptic density found in asymmetric synapses.

label.value: postsynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the postsynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.

label.value: presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the presynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a presynapse.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a postsynapse.
Any process that modulates the physical form of a presynapse.
Any process that modulates the physical form of a postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by trans-synaptic protein complex

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by a trans-synaptic complex.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trans-synaptic signaling.

label.value: regulation of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by endocanabinoid

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by an endocannabinoid.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of adhesion between pre- and post-synaptic membranes.

label.value: zinc ion import into synaptic vesicle

value.value: The directed movement of Zn2+ ions from the cytoplasm into the lumen of a cytoplasmic vesicle.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a presynapse.
The intermediate filament cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by BDNF, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the vesicular release and reception of brain derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF), that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: structural constituent of postsynaptic intermediate filament cytoskeleton

value.value: The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a postsynaptic intermediate filament cytoskeleton.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprised of intermediate filament and their associated proteins in the postsynaptic cytoskeleton.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a postsynapse.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures and their associated proteins in the presynaptic cytoskeleton.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising cytoskeletal filaments and their associated proteins in the postsynaptic cytoskeleton.
The portion of the spectrin-associated cytoskeleton contained within the postsynapse.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of spectrin-associated cytoskeleton and associated proteins in the postsynapse.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF) crossing the synaptic cleft.

label.value: cerebellar Golgi cell to granule cell synapse

value.value: A synapse formed by a cerebellar Golgi cell synapsing on to a cerebellar granule cell.
The component of the synaptic membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to one of its surfaces, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.

A membrane microdomain that forms a necklace around the bulb (crater) of a caveola. Intramembrane particles are concentrated in this region and cytoskeletal components, including actin, are highly enriched in the area underlying it.
The region of a caveola that extends into the cytoplasm, excluding the neck (rim). This region is associated with intracellular caveola proteins.
Development of a plant organ, a multi-tissue plant structure that forms a functional unit.

label.value: maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion, telomeric

value.value: The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome along the length of the telomeric region is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate during a mitotic cell cycle.
The cell cycle process in which telomeres of sister chromatids are joined during mitosis.
Fusion of the membrane of a vesicle with the plasma membrane, thereby releasing its contents into the extracellular space.
The lipid bilayer surrounding an exocytic vesicle.

label.value: calcium-dependent activation of synaptic vesicle fusion

value.value: The regulatory process by which increased cytosolic calcium levels lead to the the fusion of synaptic vesicles with the presynaptic active zone membrane by bringing primed synaptic vesicle membrane into contact with membrane presynaptic active zone membrane.
A cytoplasmic, membrane bound vesicle that is capable of fusing to the plasma membrane to release its contents into the extracellular space.

A biological process in which synaptic vesicles are loaded with neurotransmitters, move to the active zone, exocytose and are then recycled via endocytosis, ultimately leading to reloading with neurotransmitters.
Any process that modulates the potential difference across a presynaptic membrane.

label.value: synaptic vesicle transport along actin filament

value.value: The directed movement of synaptic vesicles along actin filaments within a cell, powered by molecular motors.

label.value: ligand-gated monoatomic ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Any ligand-gated ion channel activity, occurring in the presynaptic membrane, that is involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential.

label.value: voltage-gated monoatomic ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Voltage-gated ion channel activity, occurring in the presynaptic membrane, involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential. This is a key step in synaptic transmission, following the arrival of an action potential at the synapse.

label.value: regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: Any process that regulates the concentration of calcium in the presynaptic cytosol.

label.value: calcium ion binding involved in regulation of cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: The directed change of cytosolic calcium ion concentration in the cytosol via the reversible binding of calcium ions to calcium-binding proteins in the cytosol thereby modulating the spatial and temporal dynamics of changes in cytosolic calcium concentrations.
